article.headline: Bradley 64, Jackson St. 55
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- Andrew Warren scored 23 points Monday night as Bradley beat Jackson State 64-55. Bradley made 9 of 14 shots from the field as the Braves (5-5) shot 56 percent. Jordan Prosser had 10 points and seven rebounds for Bradley, which led by as many as 20 points in the first half and held a 32-20 edge at halftime. Tyrone Hanson had 22 points and Grant Maxey 16 for the Tigers (4-8). Hanson made a pair of early 3-pointers to put Jackson State ahead 6-5, but the Tigers didn't lead again. It was the first meeting between the schools.
